                {
                    "node": {
                        "created_at": "1724988450",
                        "id": "18035438225168134",
                        "text": "A life-changing Michelin 3-star cheesecake \ud83e\uddc0\n\n\u30df\u30b7\u30e5\u30e9\u30f3\u4e09\u3064\u661f\u5c4b\u306e\u30c1\u30fc\u30ba\u30b1\u30fc\u30ad\n\nChef @kishidashuzo of Tokyo\u2019s famed Michelin 3-star French restaurant Quintessence first developed this one-of-a-kind cheesecake as a way to keep his staff and restaurant afloat during the pandemic. Unwilling to settle for anything less than perfect, Chef Kishida spent years perfecting his recipe.\n\nThis three-layer cheesecake starts with a tart base full of dried nuts, followed by a middle layer of rare cheesecake blended with cream cheese and sour cream, and finally a top layer of baked cheesecake made with rare 36-month-aged Comt\u00e9 cheese.\n\nEach layer creates a specific balance and harmony between sweetness and acidity, texture and mouthfeel, and form and function.\n\nA single bite will challenge everything you know about cheesecakes, as you experience the vast difference that 17 consecutive years of Michelin 3-star excellence makes.\n\nThe cake is available for delivery only and can be ordered via @omakasejapan.\n\n\ud83c\udff7\ufe0f \u00a55400 \u30ac\u30c8\u30fc\u30aa\u30fc\u30b3\u30f3\u30c6 G\u00e2teau Au Comt\u00e9\n\n\ud83d\udccd Quintessence \u30ab\u30f3\u30c6\u30b5\u30f3\u30b9 (6 Chome-7-29 Kitashinagawa, Shinagawa City, Tokyo 140-0001, Japan)\n\n#cheesecake #tokyoeats #\u6771\u4eac\u30b9\u30a4\u30fc\u30c4"
                    }
                }
            ]
        },
